Europe's heart, Germany represents a quarter of the EU's production, but it is in recession for the second consecutive year and is likely to be third. In 2024, GDP fell by 0.2 percent, after contraction in 2023 was 0.3%. The export, ace in the German industry's sleeve, is in severe crisis, as a result of the collapse of the manufacturing industry and the automotive industry, with Volkswagen who announced the cut of 35,000 jobs by 2030. The construction sector is also braking, blocked by inaccessible costs for those who want to build their own home. There is then the issue of immigration and security, perceived within the country increasingly out of control. Less than a week from the vote, the new polls > give the Christian-conservers of Merz around 30%, Weidel's AfD over 20%, the Spd at 16% and the Greens just below 13%. It closes the surprising 7% of the Linke - which in this way could beat its former leader Sahra Wagenknecht (founder of the BSW, at 4%) - and 5% relocated to enter the Bundestag of the Liberal Party of Lindner.
